President Joe Biden has announced his intention to nominate Kiran Ahuja as Director of the Office of Personnel Management (OPM). Ahuja has over two decades of experience in public service and leadership in the nonprofit/philanthropic sector. She currently serves as CEO of Philanthropy Northwest, a regional network of philanthropic institutions. Ahuja began her career as a civil rights lawyer at the U.S. Department of Justice, focusing on school desegregation cases and racial harassment. She later served as the executive director of the National Asian Pacific American Women's Forum and as the executive director of the White House Initiative on Asian Americans and Pacific Islanders during the Obama-Biden Administration. Ahuja has also worked as the chief of staff at the U.S. Office of Personnel Management. She grew up in Savannah, Georgia, as an Indian immigrant and holds a bachelor's degree in political science from Spelman College and a law degree from the University of Georgia.